<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11146i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11146i">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11146i"> 146(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ Turkish bath <font color="green">[Dubl]</font> / (Dr Ptk Joyce, Kilkenny)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The recent discussion about <mark>Turkish baths</mark> recalls to a correspondent their originator in Dublin, Dr. Achmet Borumborard, the first Turk who ever walked our streets in native costume. <font color="green">[...]</font> The doctor fell in love with a Miss Hartigan, who declined to marry him unless he shaved and became a Christian. He shaved, reappeared, fell upon his knees before her, and cried, &ldquo;Don&apos;t be angry, my dear creature! To tell the honest truth, I am as good a Christian as the Archbishop. I&apos;m your own countryman, <mark>Mr. Patrick Joyce from Kilkenny</mark> County&mdash;the devil a Turk any more than yourself.&rdquo; <small> <a name="FJ14jul24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FJ14jul24"><cite title="source">Freeman's Journal</cite></a> (14 July 1924) 8/6</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
